{"word":"ὑπερδεής","slug":"ὑπερδεής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n107383\" key=\"u(perdeh/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὑπερδεής</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ές</itype>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp> acc. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπερδέᾰ,</foreign> for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπερδεέα</foreign>: (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">δέος</etym>):—<sense id=\"n107383.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">above all fear, undaunted,</tr_> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὑπερδέα δῆμον ἔχοντας</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:17:330\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17.330</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> </bibl> ad loc.; but <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Apollon.\">Apollon.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lex.\">Lex.</a></title_></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author></bibl>, derive it from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">δέομαι</foreign> (to want), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">much less, inferior</tr_>: neither expl. is satisfactory and Brocks' cj. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπὲρ Δία</foreign> should perh. be accepted.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}